<s> My comments are preceded by CL::  </s>
<s> CL:: My quick response is that references to background images and colours were removed from the checklist and guideline for two reasons: 1) colour and background issues are well covered in most general style guides, and more importantly,  </s>
<s> 2) if all other accessibility guidelines are met, then colour choices and  </s>
<s> background images are not really barriers since people who can see them can control their display via their browsers (or personal style sheets).  </s>
<s> Since the concept of controlling colours and background display through the browser is not anything the page-author needs to worry about, it really doesn't have to be mentioned in the guidelines.  </s>
<s> It might be a good idea to remind browser manufacturers not to ever remove the ability to control them from their software -- but that is for the UI group to deal with.  </s>
<s> If someone writes a "guideline for browser users", then that item would be an important inclusion.  </s>
